### Typography System

Font pairing:

- Titles and metrics: `Manrope`
- Body, forms, tables: `Source Sans 3`
- IDs, VIN fragments, SKUs, times, financial and utility data: `IBM Plex Mono`

Type scale:

- Page title: `40/44` desktop, `34/40` tablet, `28/34` mobile, weight `750-800`, tracking `-0.03em`
- Section header: `24/30`, weight `700`, tracking `-0.02em`
- Card title: `18/24`, weight `650-700`
- Body: `15/22`
- Large body: `16/24`
- Compact body and table meta: `13/18`
- Labels: `12/16`, weight `600`
- Helper text: `13/18`
- Eyebrow: `11/16`, uppercase, tracking `0.12em`, weight `700`
- Metric numbers: `34/36` standard, `44/44` hero, tabular numerals, weight `700-800`

Rules:

- Tight line-height on titles: `1.05-1.15`
- Body line-height: `1.45`
- Utility and meta line-height: `1.3`
- Avoid decorative display effects on operational type

### Layout System

- Standard page max width: `1440px`
- Command and operations modules can expand to `1600-1680px`
- Grid: `12` columns desktop, `8` tablet, `4` mobile
- Gutters: `24px` desktop, `20px` tablet, `16px` mobile
- Major section spacing: `32-40px`
- Related panel spacing: `20-24px`
- Utility grouping spacing: `12-16px`
- Panel padding: `20px` default, `16px` compact, `28px` hero

Density strategy:

- High information usefulness without feeling cramped
- No oversized whitespace for visual theater
- Dense work should become structured, not sparse

Responsive philosophy:

- Preserve task order before aesthetic symmetry
- Keep filters and actions visible and grouped
- Side rails should collapse only when necessary

### Radius, Borders, and Elevation

Radius scale:

- `8`
- `12`
- `16`
- `20`
- `999`

Elevation:

- `elevation-0`: flat workspace surfaces
- `elevation-1`: grouped panels and toolbars
- `elevation-2`: drawers
- `elevation-3`: modals

Usage rules:

- Use tonal separation first, shadows second
- Prefer flat bordered work surfaces for tables and dense editors
- Use elevation to distinguish overlays and high-priority support surfaces, not as decoration

### Interaction System

State behavior:

- Hover: subtle contrast lift and optional slight elevation on interactive panels
- Pressed: darken `6-8%`, reduce elevation
- Selected: fill plus border plus text shift together
- Focus: `2px` outer ring plus border shift

Timing:

- Hover transitions: `120ms`
- Control state transitions: `180ms`
- Panel and drawer transitions: `220ms`
- Route-level transitions: `280ms`

Motion style:

- Short, directional, friction-aware
- Use fade plus `8-12px` travel
- Avoid springy, playful motion

Dispatch drag and drop:

- Lifted card shadow
- Lane glow on valid targets
- Conflict warning tint for invalid or overloaded states
- Snap-to-slot settle on drop

### Density Strategy by Module

- Overview: balanced
- Customers: compact
- Vehicles: compact
- Jobs: balanced-compact
- Dispatch: dense
- Parts: balanced-dense
- Inventory: balanced-dense
- Detail workspaces: balanced header, dense primary canvas, compact support rails

### Do and Don't Rules

Do:

- Use one clear primary action per region
- Differentiate registry, queue, command-center, and detail workspace page types
- Keep accent color meaningful and scarce
- Make statuses, timings, and metrics feel authoritative
- Make empty states specific and actionable

Don't:

- Use bright blue as identity
- Use giant padding that kills density
- Let every panel look identical
- Mix legacy `workspace-*` styling with new system patterns
- Use glossy gradients, playful iconography, or oversized radii
- Rely on color alone for critical state

## Front-End Implementation Plan

### Existing Technical Seams

The implementation should route through the existing design and shell seams:

- `packages/core/src/design/tokens.ts`
- `apps/web/app/design-system.css`
- `apps/web/app/globals.css`
- `apps/web/components/ui/*`
- `apps/web/app/dashboard/layout.tsx`

The central rule is to turn the `ui-*` shared layer into the only shared visual language over time and retire legacy `workspace-*` styling patterns.

### Global CSS and Token Architecture

Source of truth:

- Keep authored design tokens in `packages/core/src/design/tokens.ts`
- Generate runtime CSS custom properties from that token source

Authoring layers:

1. `base`
2. `shell`
3. `components`
4. `patterns`
5. `modules`

Rules:

- `globals.css` should only handle resets, root defaults, browser normalization, and font smoothing
- `design-system.css` should own visual styling
- Modules may define workflow-specific layout, but shared primitives must not be re-skinned locally
- No new legacy `workspace-*` styles should be introduced

